{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory police recording of where child abduction/coercion began online",
        "additional_details": "Police forces report rising levels of online grooming, yet there is no national system to track when digital communication leads to a child being persuaded, coerced, or moved.\r\nWe believe recording this information would:\r\n- improve national understanding of online enabled risks\r\n- support evidence based safeguarding policies\r\n- help police identify patterns and intervene earlier\r\n- strengthen child protection across the UK\r\nWe want Government to introduce a statutory duty for police forces to record online involvement in abduction cases.",
        "background": "We believe recording this information would:\r\n- improve national understanding of online enabled risks\r\n- support evidence based safeguarding policies\r\n- help police identify patterns and intervene earlier\r\n- strengthen child protection\r\nData is not routinely collected on if abductions begin online",
